{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Jz1nQvuG6hsjd7DLHs3u65","type":"tool_result","content":"Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\ncreamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\nSeason with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n\nCARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n\nSlice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\nlemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n\nPreparation: 10 minutes\nServes: 4\n\nCARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n\nPlace thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\noil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\nthinly sliced radish.\n\nnto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\nwith damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ae7c1124-3c84-467a-af52-dc284b447f62","uuid":"cc79a8f5-81fb-41dd-a1a6-1fc2d9d0ed7c","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\ncreamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\nSeason with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n\nCARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n\nSlice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\nlemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n\nPreparation: 10 minutes\nServes: 4\n\nCARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n\nPlace thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\noil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\nthinly sliced radish.\n\nnto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\nwith damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
